Sharon,

I don&#39;t know about Bruce&#39;s experience with Lisa but I can tell you that there are usually many voices overlayed in a single recording. This multilayered effect is what most of the time, allows people to hear different messages in the same recording depending on their ears frequency response (one stands out more than the other or not at all).

When I use a scanning method such as the many boxes ya&#39;ll mention, I  have never had a problem telling the difference between a male and female voice. I use more than one radio though when using this method (I use 3 with a mixer).

Regards,

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: mllejade &lt;leongbabe@...&gt;
