Subject: [EVP-ITC] Male and female voices joined to create one response?














            Bruce,



Is it common to receive a response comprised of a mixture of men and 

women sound bytes/voices (like I heard in this one)?  My guess is 

that we hear predominantly male voices because they&#39;re more male 

radio announcers.  Therefore, does the entity who announces herself 

to you as Lisa come through with a male voice at times (because those 

are the voices that she gets most of the time to formulate a 

response)?  Please tell me if my reasoning here is way off base...



Thanks,

Sharon



